# Select columns needed for analysis

comcast_complaints_state_tbl2 <- comcast_complaints_tbl %>%
    select("Customer Complaint", Date, "Received Via", City, State, Status) %>%
    set_names(names(.) %>% str_replace(" ","_")) %>%

# Fix typo: correct naming in state column
    mutate(State = case_when(State == "District of Columbia" ~ 
                             "District Of Columbia",  TRUE~State))%>%
    
# Create a new column for status using only "open" and "closed"
    mutate(Status2 = case_when(
        Status =="Open"~"Open",
        Status =="Pending"~"Open",
        Status =="Closed"~"Closed",
        Status =="Solved"~"Closed"
    ))

# Frequency table with number of complaints by state

table_number_by_state_tbl <- comcast_complaints_state_tbl2 %>%
    select(Customer_Complaint, State, Status2)%>%
    group_by(State, Status2) %>%
    tally()

table_number_by_state_tbl
# Visual of complaints by state and status with flipped coordinates

    geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
    aes(x=State, y=n, fill=Status2) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = percent) +
    coord_flip()

    select(Customer_Complaint, Status2, State) %>%
    group_by(State, Status2) %>%

# Load topic models  and tm packages
library(tm)
library(topicmodels)

# Create corpus
comcast_complaints1 <- read_excel("Comcast_Telecom_Complaints_data.xlsx")

# Vector of Complaints
comcast_complaints <- comcast_complaints1$`Customer Complaint`

# View first 5 complaints
head(comcast_complaints, 5)
## [1] "Comcast Cable Internet Speeds"                                    
## [2] "Payment disappear - service got disconnected"                     
## [3] "Speed and Service"                                                
## [4] "Comcast Imposed a New Usage Cap of 300GB that punishes streaming."
## [5] "Comcast not working and no service to boot"
# Make a vector source: complaint source
complaint_source <- VectorSource(comcast_complaints)

# Make a volatile corpus: complaint corpus from complaint_source
complaint_corpus <- VCorpus(complaint_source)

# Alter the function code to apply pre-processing
clean_corpus <- function(corpus) {
# Remove punctuation
complaint_corpus <- tm_map(complaint_corpus, removePunctuation)
  
# Transform to lower case
complaint_corpus <- tm_map(complaint_corpus, tolower)
# Add more stopwords
complaint_corpus <- tm_map(complaint_corpus, removeWords, 
                           words = c(stopwords("en"), "comcast", "xfinity"))
  # Strip whitespace
  complaint_corpus <- tm_map(complaint_corpus, stripWhitespace)
  return(complaint_corpus)
}

# Generate DTM
complaint_dtm <- DocumentTermMatrix(complaint_corpus)

# convert rownames to file names - use vector name
rownames(complaint_dtm) <- comcast_complaints

# collapse matrix by summing over columns
freq <- colSums(as.matrix(complaint_dtm))

# length should be total number of terms
length(freq)
## [1] 1725
# Create sort order descending
ord <- order(freq,decreasing = TRUE)

# Run LDA using Gibbs sampling
ldaOut <-LDA(complaint_dtm,3, method="Gibbs")

# Write out results
# docs to topics
ldaOut.topics <- as.matrix(topics(ldaOut))
write.csv(ldaOut.topics,"DocsToTopics.csv")

# Top 6 terms in each topic
ldaOut.terms <- as.matrix(terms(ldaOut,6))
write.csv(ldaOut.terms,"TopicsToTerms.csv")

# probabilities associated with each topic assignment
topicProbabilities <- as.data.frame(ldaOut@gamma)
write.csv(topicProbabilities,"TopicProbabilities.csv")

# Find relative importance of top 2 topics
topic1ToTopic2 <- lapply(1:nrow(complaint_dtm),function(x)
sort(topicProbabilities[x,])[3]/sort(topicProbabilities[x,])[3-1])
 
# Find relative importance of third most important topic
topic2ToTopic3 <- lapply(1:nrow(complaint_dtm),function(x)
sort(topicProbabilities[x,])[3-1]/sort(topicProbabilities[x,])[3-2])
 
# write to file
write.csv(topic1ToTopic2,"Topic1ToTopic2.csv")
write.csv(topic2ToTopic3,"Topic2ToTopic3.csv")

# Create tbl from csv file
DocsToTopics_tbl <- read.csv("DocsToTopics.csv")

# Join tables by the "complaint
topic_table_tbl <- left_join(comcast_complaints_state_tbl2,DocsToTopics_tbl,
                             by=c("Customer_Complaint" = "X")) 

# Create a new column & rename the observations by the three type: service, billing, and data
topic_table_tbl%>%
  mutate(Complaint_type = (case_when(
    V1 == "1" ~"Service",
    V1 == "2" ~"Data",
    V1 == "3" ~ "Billing"
  ))) %>%

# Create a table that shows the frequency of each complaint type    
   select(Customer_Complaint, Complaint_type)%>%
   group_by(Complaint_type) %>%
   tally() %>%
   mutate(percentage = (n/sum(n))*100)
